│ from attempting this unsafe transformation.                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The bug is a miscompilation due to the SLP vectorizer incorrectly transforming a series of │
│ scalar `select` and `or` instructions into a vector reduction, which does not preserve the │
│ original `poison` semantics. The proposed fix is to disable this specific horizontal       │
│ reduction pattern when it involves `select` instructions. This is a conservative but safe  │
│ solution that resolves the correctness issue. More advanced analysis could potentially     │
│ enable vectorization in some of these cases, but for now, correctness is paramount.        │
