│ The bug is a miscompilation caused by the SLP vectorizer's horizontal reduction logic. It  │
│ incorrectly vectorizes a chain of scalar `select` and `or` instructions, which can be      │
│ viewed as a logical OR reduction. The `select` instruction has short-circuiting semantics  │
│ with respect to `poison`: if the condition is determined, the value of the unused branch   │
│ (even if `poison`) does not affect the result. The vectorized version, however, evaluates  │
│ all scalar operations unconditionally within a vector, and then performs a vector          │
│ reduction. This can propagate `poison` from an operand that would have been ignored in the │
│ scalar version, leading to a result that is more poisonous than the original, which is a   │
│ correctness violation.                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root of the problem lies in how the vectorizer identifies reduction candidates. The    │
│ function `HorizontalReduction::getRdxKind` uses `m_LogicalOr` and `m_LogicalAnd` matchers, │
│ which treat `select` instructions as logical operations. This is generally correct for     │
│ value semantics, but not for `poison` semantics.                                           │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to prevent `getRdxKind` from matching `select`-based logical operations         │
│ (`m_LogicalOr`, `m_LogicalAnd`). By removing these matchers, we ensure that `select`       │
│ instructions are not considered part of a logical `and`/`or` reduction chain, thus         │
│ avoiding the miscompilation. This change is targeted and safer than disabling all          │
│ `select`-based reductions, as it still allows for valid reductions like `min`/`max` which  │
│ are also implemented with `select` instructions but have different semantics.              │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -18709,12 +18709,13 @@                                                                  │
│        return RecurKind::Add;                                                              │
│      if (match(I, m_Mul(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                            │
│        return RecurKind::Mul;                                                              │
│ -    if (match(I, m_And(m_Value(), m_Value())) ||                                          │
│ -        match(I, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                     │
│ +    // NOTE: We do not use m_LogicalAnd/m_LogicalOr for horizontal reductions             │
│ +    // because they are not safe in the presence of poison. A select-based                │
│ +    // logical op can mask poison, but a vectorized reduction would not.                  │
│ +    if (match(I, m_And(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                            │
│        return RecurKind::And;                                                              │
│ -    if (match(I, m_Or(m_Value(), m_Value())) ||                                           │
│ -        match(I, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                      │
│ +    if (match(I, m_Or(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                             │
│        return RecurKind::Or;                                                               │
│      if (match(I, m_Xor(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                            │
│        return RecurKind::Xor;                                                              │
│      if (match(I, m_FAdd(m_Value(), m_Value())))                                           │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
